enum WNClientAuthState

WNClient authentication state.

Enumerator:
WNClientAuthStateLoggedOut 

The client is not logged in.

WNClientAuthStateLoggingIn 

The client is in the process of logging in.

WNClientAuthStateLoggedIn 

The client has successfully logged in.

enum WNDataSourceSelectionPolicy

WNCompositeWordDataSource codes for the active policy in data source selection.

Enumerator:
WNUseOnlineWhenReachablePolicy 

Use the online data sources if they are reachable.

WNUseOnlineOnlyPolicy 

Use the online data sources only, do not use offline data source.

WNUseOfflinePreferredPolicy 

Use the offline data sources first, if the word is not present, then go online if reachable.

WNUseDefaultPolicy 

Default policy is WNUseOnlineWhenReachablePolicy.

enum WNErrorCode

NSError codes in the WNErrorDomain.

Enumerator:
WNErrorCodeUnknown 

An unknown error occured.

Any use of this error code should be considered a bug.

WNErrorCodeConnectionFailed 

The request failed due to a network, server, or other communications error.

WNErrorCodeInvalidResponse 

The request failed due to an invalid response received from the server.

WNErrorCodeRequestConflict 

The request failed due to a conflict with an existing request.

WNErrorCodeAuthenticatedFailed 

Authentication to the remote server or resource failed.

WNErrorCodeRequestGeneralError 

The server returned an error result for the request, but a more specific error code is unavailable.

Additional information may be available via the WNErrorServerMessageKey.

WNErrorCodeDatabaseQueryFailed 

The request failed due to a database query failure.

WNErrorCodeNoDataSourcesAvailable 

The request failed due to no available data sources.
